05-27-2017 14-42-37 Mohamed Miraoui Salam team. I wanted to take a moment to remind us all to set goals for ourselves this Ramadan, if we haven't already. It can be helpful to choose a bad habit we want to eliminate in our lives and a good habit we want to develop. Given that Ramadan is the month of the Quran, it might also be helpful to set Quranic goals. Perhaps we want to read the entire Quran once this Ramadan (20 pages a day). Let's also not forget to dedicate some time to understanding the Quran as well, being sure to dedicate time daily to reading translation or listening to an easy tafseer (Nouman Ali Khan has some on YouTube and on the Podcast app on iPhone, under the Bayyinah Channel). Let's also not forget to give some time to memorizing Quran, no matter how small the amount (even a line a day), or reviewing what we've previously memorized.
05-27-2017 14-51-12 Mohamed Miraoui Ramadan is a gift and an absolute gem. It's a time to cleanse ourselves and make changes in our lives. It's a time to discover the true beauty of ibadah, as well as patience and discipline. It's a time to develop a lasting relationship with the Quran, something I remind myself of first before anyone else. It's a month that shows us the fruits that come with struggle, for the sake of Allah SWT. We need to push ourselves this month InshaAllah, we have a huge opportunity ahead of us. Let's limit the time we spend on social media, TV, shows, etc. Let's make a sincere intention to benefit from this Ramadan and grow in our Iman
05-27-2017 14-56-39 Mohamed Miraoui The final piece of advice I'll give is for us all to not burn ourselves out. Yes, we want to make use of every moment in Ramadan, but keep in mind it's an entire month. Allah SWT loves that which is less but consistent. So let's be ambitious, but realistic. And let's ask Allah SWT to give us strength and consistency. May Allah SWT make us all from those who truly benefit from this Ramadan. May He SWT allow us to exit it having changed ourselves for the better and having grown in our Islam and our Iman. Ramadan Kareem team :)

08-25-2017 16-16-18 Ali Haider Salaam This will be a bit off the rails from our ongoing discussion at the moment, but I wanted to send this message early to give ample time for responses before the semester begins. As many of you know, one of the responsibilities of the Academic Director is to run the tutoring service that the MSA provides for its members. Ahead from managing it though, much of the contribution usually ends up being led by the Shura and General Body as a whole. This past year, however, we had a low number of tutors, and were unfortunately unable to continue the program. One of my goals for Fall is to start over fresh, and again provide this as a service. To do this though, we’re going to need tutors, and I’d hope that some of you would volunteer Inshallah.
08-25-2017 16-16-26 Ali Haider In general, the commitment is low, and you work entirely off of your schedule. As a small comment, don’t feel inhibited by expectations that people might have for you. Often times, students are just looking for guidance, and don’t expect you to reteach the entire course.

10-14-2017 21-21-16 Amina Bendaoud Salam, I had an idea for one of the topics. So one of the names of Allah SWT is the loving. And we hear time and time again how we should love each other for the sake of Allah SWT and how none of us is a believer until we love for our brothers and sisters what we want for ourselves. And I think a major problem in academics especially college is severe competitiveness between each other where people sadly don't get happy at the success of their friends and sometimes even wish for them to do badly because they think it will impact their own success. So I think one of the topics should be about truly embodying what it means to love our brothers and sisters and that we should sincerely pray for their success and happiness.
10-14-2017 21-21-24 Amina Bendaoud To tie it to the theme, the goal isn't to cross the finish line, it's to be the type of person that wishes for everyone to cross the finish line (I realize how extremely cheesy that sounds so if we could say it in a different way, that'd be great lol) but yeah even though the topic is cliche I think it ties in with our theme and is extremely relevant to college students, especially since I always hear people referring to college as a rat race cause it's so competitive. So if Zaid Abbassi chooses to talk about the loving, that could be the topic. Idk on the flyer what the actual name for the topic would be though.

11-21-2017 22-11-40 Eggsecutive I was thinking to have a team dodgeball/kappadi night Team dodgeball is pretty self explanatory, but I can explain the rules more later if necessary Kappadi is a game where there's an imaginary line dividing two teams and one guy from team A has to go and tag as many people as he can from team B and come back all while saying the word "kappadi" If he stops saying it on the other side because he runs out of breath or because the other team has grabbed him and restrained him, he's out.
11-21-2017 22-12-15 Eggsecutive Team A and B alternate until one team wins
11-21-2017 22-12-42 Eggsecutive A game with both the intellectual challenge of strategy as well as physical action
11-21-2017 22-16-10 Eggsecutive If that sounded confusing I can send you a link with better directions or a kappadi montage, but I think you'll get the idea. If it's not too chaotic maybe we can get to advertising the idea?
